**Fix 1 (Line 195):** `variant={ButtonVariant.secondary}` — The type of `variant` changed to add `'stateful'`. The value `secondary` is still valid in the new type, so **no code change is needed**. The value `'secondary'` exists in both the old and new union types.

**Fix 2 (Line 192):** Icon children should be moved to the `icon` prop. Looking at the Button on lines 192-199:

```tsx
<Button
  onClick={handleCheckService}
  disabled={loading}
  variant={ButtonVariant.secondary}
  style={{ marginRight: '5px' }}
>
  {t('Rediscover')}
</Button>
```

This Button contains **only text** (`{t('Rediscover')}`), not an icon element. There are no icon imports from `@patternfly/react-icons` in this file. The rule fired based on the component being a `<Button>`, but the actual content is just text — there's no icon to move. **No code change is needed.**

